cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with visual inpainting, which is a computer vision problem. The use of convolutional context encoders and adversarial training suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of perceptual reconstruction losses and optimization-based refinement suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The fact that the paper deals with visual scenes suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
